umman G-44 Widgeon]] \u2013 ''N404Q'' \u2013 On display at the [[Florida Air Museum]] at [[Lakeland Linder International Airport]].\n*[[Grumman J2F Duck]] \u2013 ''N1214N ''- A second Duck is in storage awaiting restoration.\n*[[Grumman TBF Avenger|Grumman TBM-3E Avenger]] \u2013 ''N9548Z''\n*[[Hawker Tempest|Hawker Tempest II]] \u2013 ''N607LA'' \u2013 Under restoration at Fanatsy of Flight\n*[[Hawker Tempest|Hawker Tempest V]] \u2013 \"EJ693\" \u2013 Under restoration at Fantasy of Flight\n*[[Hiller Hornet]] \u2013 ''N125JC'' \u2013 The 13th of the 17 aircraft built and currently the only flyable example.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fantasyofflight.com/aircraftpages/hornet.htm|title=Hiller Hornet|first=|last=Clark/Nikdel/Powell|website=Fantasy of Flight|accessdate=29 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Ben Howard (aviator)#Aircraft Racing|Howard DGA-5 \"Ike\"]] \u2013 ''reproduction''\n*[[Junkers Ju 52]] \u2013 \"G-BFHG\" \u2013 Formerly owned by Aces High Ltd based at [[North Weald Airfield]]. Currently in storage.\n*[[Kawasaki Ki-61|Kawasaki Ki-61 Hien]] \u2013 Disassembled and awaiting long-term restoration. Currently in storage.\n*Kingfisher - Under restoration Auckland, New Zealand.\n*[[Laird Super Solution]] \u2013 ''reproduction'' \u2013 The only flying example of this aircraft in the world.\n*[[Lavochkin La-11]] \u2013 In storage\n*[[Lockheed Constellation|Lockheed L-1649A Starliner]] \u2013 ''N974R''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://conniesurvivors.com/N974R.htm|title=Lockheed Constellation Survivors|website=conniesurvivors.com|accessdate=29 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Lockheed P-38 Lightning|Lockheed P-38L Lightning]] \u2013 USAAF Ser. No. 44-26761 in storage as long-term restoration project.\n*[[Lockheed Vega|Lockheed Vega 5A/5C]] \u2013 ''NC105W'' \u2013 One of five remaining. Currently being restored offsite.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fantasyofflight.com/aircraftpages/vega.htm|title=Lockheed Vega|first=|last=Clark/Nikdel/Powell|website=Fantasy of Flight|accessdate=29 